>> % sys = tf(num,den) untuk menciptakan fungsi transfer waktu kontinu
% sys = zpk(z,p,k) untuk model zero pole gain di mana variabel z dan p memiliki angka zeros dan poles sistem dan k adalah penguatan
%Jika tidak ada angka zeros, gunakan z= [].
%konversi balik [z,p,k] = tf2zp(num,den) dan [num,den] = (zp2tf(z,p,k)

%Contoh 3.1

>> num = [1 1];
>> den = [1 3 1];
>> sys = tf(num,den)

sys =
 
      s + 1
  -------------
  s^2 + 3 s + 1
 
Continuous-time transfer function.
Model Properties
>> sys_zpk = zpk(sys)

sys_zpk =
 
         (s+1)
  -------------------
  (s+2.618) (s+0.382)
 
Continuous-time zero/pole/gain model.
Model Properties
>> 
>> % contoh 3.2
>> z = -2;
>> p = [-1 -1 -3]

p =

    -1    -1    -3

>> k = 1;
>> Sys = zpk(z,p,k)

Sys =
 
      (s+2)
  -------------
  (s+1)^2 (s+3)
 
Continuous-time zero/pole/gain model.
Model Properties
>> 
>> Sys_tf = tf(Sys)

Sys_tf =
 
          s + 2
  ---------------------
  s^3 + 5 s^2 + 7 s + 3
 
Continuous-time transfer function.
Model Properties
>> 
>> %contoh 3.3
>> s = tf('s');
>>  % s = 1 *1 jenis tf
>> SYS = (s+1)/(s^2 +2*s +1)

SYS =
 
      s + 1
  -------------
  s^2 + 2 s + 1
 
Continuous-time transfer function.
Model Properties
>> % Dan untuk mengembalikan fungsi transfer dalam bentuk terafaktor
>> s = zpk('s');
>> sys = (s+1)/(s^2 +2*s +1)

sys =
 
   (s+1)
  -------
  (s+1)^2
 
Continuous-time zero/pole/gain model.
Model Properties
>> 
>> % Contoh 3.4

>> s = zpk('s');
>> sys = ((s+2) * (s - 1))/(((s +3)^2) * (s-5))

sys =
 
